%h2 Take Action
%p.project-intro Challenging projects engage students, and help them develop essential competencies, innovative mindsets, and creative confidence.  These bite-size projects are tied to the real world, cut across disciplines, and can be done in a few hours or days.  Each calls for students to present their work to others, who in turn ask questions and offer constructive suggestions -- so draw on our Share Your Learning playlist item.
%p.project-intro We’d love for you to create a 1-2 minute video capturing your reflections after you “Try a Project,” and email it to us at <a href="mailto:info@mltsfilm.org">info@mltsfilm.org</a>.  We’ll curate submissions and use them to help others learn from your insights.

